criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. patients with severe intrauterine adhesions or scarring of the endometrium for whom drugs and surgical interventions were ineffective;
2. Age: 22-45 years old;
3. who is willing to accept follow-up.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Chromosome karyotype abnormalities;
2. Severe endometriosis; 
3. Severe adenomyosis;
4. Severe congenital uterine malformations;
5. Vaginitis and endometritis;
6. systemic diseases: hypertension, diabetes, and so on;
7. Contraindications to pregnancy;
8. Contraindications to hormone replacement therapy;
9. Medical history of pelvic tumors or receiving pelvic radiotherapy;
10. Unable to adhere to the hospital examination and follow-up, or carrying on other treatment during follow-up period.
